cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.CS, cs.DS

Reasoning: The paper is primarily focused on the Calculus of Conjunctive Queries (CCQ) and its foundational status in database theory, which suggests cs.DB as the most likely sub-category. However, the paper also introduces a diagrammatic language and uses category theory to derive a sound and complete axiomatisation of query inclusion, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CS (Computer Science and Game Theory), or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
